News24 Correspondent Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories A Mogale City spokesperson says a collision between a minibus taxi and a truck is the worst accident he has seen in 13 years of service. Fourteen people have died.WATCHPolokwane - Two people were killed when a taxi they were travelling in suffered a tyre burst along the R40 near Hoedspruit on Saturday.It is alleged that the taxi which was transporting people from Acornhoek to Phalaborwa had a back tyre burst and the driver lost control, resulting in it rolling and killing one passenger instantly."The second [passenger] died on arrival at the hospital and other passengers were admitted to Maphutha Malatji Hospital with serious injuries," said police spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe.The identities of the two deceased - a man and a woman - are still unknown.Anyone who can assist in their identification is urged to go to Hoedspruit Police Station.A case of culpable homicide is being investigated. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.